<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - VALVE TRAIN: PUSH RODS ,
        HYDRAULIC VALVE LIFTERS AND CAMSHAFT - Camshaft and Gear
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Camshaft and Gear</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Check Gear Backlash and Camshaft End Play</title>
            <figure id="f1200617" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1355.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Checking the Camshaft-to-Crankshaft Gear Backlash</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Dial Indicator</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft Gear</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Before removing the camshaft, check and record the camshaft gear-to-crankshaft gear
                    backlash as follows:
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Mount a dial indicator on the front of the engine.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Position the dial indicator tip on a gear tooth and remove all lash.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Place a small pry bar between the camshaft and crankcase. Lightly pry the camshaft
                        forward.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator while lightly prying the camshaft forward.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Rotate the gear by hand while lightly prying the camshaft forward. Record the amount
                        of backlash.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200618" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1356.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Checking the Camshaft End Play</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Dial Indicator</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reposition the dial indicator and check the camshaft end play as follows:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Push the camshaft toward rear of engine.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Place a small pry bar between the camshaft gear and crankcase. Lightly pry the
                        camshaft forward. Compare the dial indicator reading with the specifications.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">If the end play exceeds the specifications, replace the camshaft thrust plate.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the dial indicator.</para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
